<plot>In one catastrophic instance young Gabriel loses both Gato, his radio-controlled car, and his girlfriend. She thinks he is childish, is obsessed with Gato and shouldn't play with barbie dolls. Disappointed Gabriel throws aside his controller. Gato moves away without Gabriel knowing it. He lost everything. Fifteen years later Gabriel's girlfriend abandons him. History seems to repeat itself. She thinks he hasn't grown up and should forsake his childish dreams. Still dazzled Gabriel and his belonging are thrown out of the house. In the 'Toys' box, he finds his Gato controller. Do dreams grow as well?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?208310</url></doc>
